properties.description: The Telecom Customer Retention application is based on data from the wireless phone industry.  The application shows how a company within the wireless industry tracks customers for churn and revenue.

qMetaDef.title: Dashboard
qMetaDef.description: The Dashboard allows users to quickly analyze account and revenue data by viewing customer activations, ceased accounts and churn.

qMetaDef.title: Churn
qMetaDef.description: The Churn sheet focuses on customer retention by looking at the churn.  Churn is the percentage difference between the total number of accounts for the month minus the number of accounts that have ceased for the same month.

qMetaDef.title: Revenue
qMetaDef.description: View revenue trends by region, state and city.

qMetaDef.title: Back to School Campaign Analysis
qMetaDef.description: Did the “Back to School” phone promotion generate revenue in the Central Region?

children.text: Did the “Back to School” phone promotion generate revenue in the Central Region?
Starting in early July, our company ran a “Back to School” promotion in the Central region. We want to see if the promotion was successful.
If we look at the Central region, we can see the number of customers that have been activated over time as well as the revenue.
Now if we look at the three months since the promotion (July, August and September) we can see the effect that the promotion had.
During the three months following the campaign, we activated 15,826 customers. The net difference in customer activations was 10,251.
Looking at the three months leading up to the promotion (April, May and June) we can see that we activated 5,575 customers.
The increase in customer activations led to increased revenue the months following the campaign as well.
Taking a look at the three months prior to the campaign, we can see that revenue was $1.29M and was under projection by almost $872K.
Looking at the revenue for the three months since the promotion was launched, we can see that revenue was $3.97M which was $2.87M over the projected revenue for the Central Region.

The “Back to School” promotion that launched in July in the Central region was successful. We saw that activations increased from 5,525 for the three months prior to the promotion to 15,826 in the three months immediately following the promotion, which is an increase of 10,251 (65%) new customer activations.
The three months prior the promotion the revenue was $1.29M. We also saw that in the three months after the promotion, the revenue increased to $3.97M which is an increase of $2.87M.
This promotion was a success in the Central region and should be considered for other regions as well.

qMetaDef.title: Region-State-City
qMetaDef.description: Region, State, City drill down.

qMetaDef.title: Activation Date
qMetaDef.description: The day the account was activated.

qMetaDef.title: Cease Status
qMetaDef.description: Account status - either Active or Cease.

qMetaDef.title: Activation Month
qMetaDef.description: The month the account was activated.

qMetaDef.title: Cease Month Year
qMetaDef.description: The month and year when the service at an account has been stopped.

qMetaDef.title: Activations
qMetaDef.description: The number of customer activations.

qMeasure.qDef: If([Cease Status]='Active', Max(TOTAL [Activation Date]), [Cease Date])-[Activation Date]

qMetaDef.title: Active Days
qMetaDef.description: The number of days an account was/is active.

qMetaDef.title: Revenue Variance
qMetaDef.description: How close the revenue is to the projected revenue.

qMetaDef.title: Projected Revenue
qMetaDef.description: Projected revenue.

qMetaDef.title: Ceased Accounts
qMetaDef.description: The number of ceased accounts.

qMetaDef.title: Churn
qMetaDef.description: The difference between the total number of accounts for a timeframe minus the number of accounts that have ceased in the same timeframe.

qMetaDef.title: Avg Ceased Customer Retention
qMetaDef.description: The average number of days accounts were active before being ceased.

qMeasure.qDef: Avg(Aggr(If([Cease Status]='Active', Max(Total [Activation Date]), [Cease Date])-[Activation Date],MSISDN))

qMetaDef.title: Avg Customer Retention
qMetaDef.description: The average number of days a customer is active.

qMetaDef.title: Churn%
qMetaDef.description: The percentage of accounts that have been ceased.

qMetaDef.title: Active Accounts
qMetaDef.description: The number of active accounts.

qMetaDef.title: +\- Revenue
qMetaDef.description: The difference between the actual revenue and the projected revenue.
